nshire, Scotland":"苏格兰阿爾迪史爾斯特林","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"苏格兰艾斯爾吉爾馬爾諾可","Scotland":"苏格兰","lifeSummary":"Margaret Lindsay于1160年出生在苏格兰艾斯爾吉爾馬爾諾可。她于1190年之前与Sir Malcolm Drummond 5th Thane of Lennox在苏格兰结婚。他们至少是2个儿子的父母。她去世于大约1240年在她的家乡享年81岁。"},"hr":{"1160–about 1240":"1160.–oko 1240.","1165–1200":"1165–1200.","1190–1259":"1190.–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190.–1240","1160–1240":"1160.–1240","1190":"1190.","about 1195":"oko 1195.","1259":"1259","1200":"1200.","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160.","before 1190":"prije 1190.","about 1240":"oko 1240.","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"cs":{"1160–about 1240":"1160–okolo 1240","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190":"1190","about 1195":"okolo 1195","1259":"1259","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","before 1190":"před 1190","about 1240":"okolo 1240","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland"},"da":{"1160–about 1240":"1160–omkring 1240","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190":"1190","about 1195":"omkring 1195","1259":"1259","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","before 1190":"før 1190","about 1240":"omkring 1240","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Skotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Skotland","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Skotland","Scotland":"Skotland"},"nl":{"1160–about 1240":"1160–circa 1240","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190":"1190","about 1195":"circa 1195","1259":"1259","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","before 1190":"vóór 1190","about 1240":"circa 1240","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Schotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Schotland","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland"},"en":{"1160–about 1240":"1160–about 1240","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190":"1190","about 1195":"about 1195","1259":"1259","1200":"1200","1165":"1165","1240":"1240","1283":"1283","1195":"1195","1160":"1160","before 1190":"before 1190","about 1240":"about 1240","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland","Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Stirling, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Lindsay","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Lindsey in Lincolnshire, England. This is first found in the form <i>Lindissi</i>, apparently a derivative of the British name of   Lincoln  . To this was later added the Old English element <i>ēg</i> ‘island’, since the place was virtually cut off by the surrounding fenland. The surname was taken to Scotland at an early date and is the name of an important and powerful Scottish family.","Irish: adopted as an equivalent ofvarious Gaelic names (see   Lindsey  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Linzy","meanings":["Altered form of Scottish, Irish, or English   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  . Compare   Lenzy  ."]},{"name":"Linzey","meanings":["English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  ."]},{"name":"Lindsey","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Lindsay  .","Irish: shortened and Anglicized form of various Gaelic surnames, as for example <b>Ó Loingsigh</b> (see   Lynch   1), <b>Mac Giolla Fhionntóg</b> (see   McClintock  ), and <b>Ó Fhloinn</b> (see   Flynn   and   Lynn  )."]},{"name":"Lincoln","meanings":["English: habitational name from the city of Lincoln, so named from an original British name <i>Lindo-</i> ‘lake’ + Latin <i>colonia</i> ‘settlement, colony’. The place was an important administrative center during the Roman occupation of Britain and in the Middle Ages it was a center for the manufacture of cloth, including the famous ‘Lincoln green’.","African American: adoption of the surname in 1 above, in honor of Abraham Lincoln, the 16th president of the US, who abolished slavery.","History: Abraham Lincoln (1809–65), 16th president of the US, was the son of an illiterate laborer, descended from Samuel Lincoln, who had emigrated from England to MA in 1637."]},{"name":"Linsey","meanings":["Scottish, Irish, or English: variant of   Lindsay   or   Lindsey  .","Americanized form of German   Linse   or Swiss German <b>Linsi</b>, see   Lins  ."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Lindsay was born in 1160, in Kilmarnock, Ayrshire, Scotland. She married Sir Malcolm Drummond 5th Thane of Lennox before 1190, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died about 1240, in her hometown, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1160–about 1240":"1160–umbes 1240","1165–1200":"1165–1200","1190–1259":"1190–1259","1195–1283":"1195–1283","1190–1240":"1190–1240","1160–1240":"1160–1240","1190":"1190","about 1195":"umbes 1195","1259":"1259